{title}My First RML Lesson{.title}

{success}Welcome to your first RML lesson! Let's learn step by step.{.success}

{lesson}
{subtitle}What is RML?{.subtitle}

{text}RML stands for {bold}RazzMarkupLanguage{.bold}. It's a simple way to create web pages without the complex HTML syntax.{.text}

{info}RML uses curly braces {} and dots (.) to make tags easy to understand.{.info}

{example}
{text}Instead of writing: {code}<h1>Title</h1>{.code}{.text}
{text}You write: {code}{title}Title{.title}{.code}{.text}
{text}Much easier, right?{.text}
{.example}
{.lesson}

{lesson}
{subtitle}Basic Tags{.subtitle}

{text}Here are the most important tags you'll use:{.text}

{table}
{row}
    {headercell}Tag{.headercell}
    {headercell}What it does{.headercell}
    {headercell}Example{.headercell}
{.row}
{row}
    {cell}{code}{title}{.code}{.cell}
    {cell}Big heading{.cell}
    {cell}{code}{title}My Page{.title}{.code}{.cell}
{.row}
{row}
    {cell}{code}{text}{.code}{.cell}
    {cell}Regular text{.cell}
    {cell}{code}{text}Hello world{.text}{.code}{.cell}
{.row}
{row}
    {cell}{code}{bold}{.code}{.cell}
    {cell}Bold text{.cell}
    {cell}{code}{bold}Important{.bold}{.code}{.cell}
{.row}
{row}
    {cell}{code}{list}{.code}{.cell}
    {cell}Bullet list{.cell}
    {cell}{code}{list}{item}Item{.item}{.list}{.code}{.cell}
{.row}
{.table}
{.lesson}

{exercise}
{bold}Your First Exercise{.bold}

{text}Create a simple page about yourself using these tags:{.text}

{orderedlist}
    {item}Use {code}{title}{.code} for your name{.item}
    {item}Use {code}{text}{.code} to describe yourself{.item}
    {item}Use {code}{list}{.code} for your hobbies{.item}
    {item}Use {code}{bold}{.code} to highlight something important{.item}
{.orderedlist}

{tip}Save your file with a .rml extension and open it in Chrome!{.tip}
{.exercise}

{quiz}
{bold}Quick Quiz{.bold}

{question}1. What symbol comes before the closing tag name?{.question}
{answer}A dot (.) - Example: {code}{.title}{.code}{.answer}

{question}2. How do you make text bold?{.question}
{answer}Use the {code}{bold}{.code} tag{.answer}

{question}3. What's the main difference between RML and HTML?{.question}
{answer}RML uses curly braces {} instead of angle brackets < >{.answer}
{.quiz}

{homework}
{bold}Homework Assignment{.bold}

